23#include "dtc.h"
24
25#include <dirent.h>
26#include <sys/stat.h>
27
28static struct node *read_fstree(const char *dirname)
29{
30 DIR *d;
31 struct dirent *de;
32 struct stat st;
33 struct node *tree;
34
35 d = opendir(dirname);
36 if (!d)
37 die("Couldn't opendir() \"%s\": %s\n", dirname, strerror(errno));
38
39 tree = build_node(NULL, NULL);
40
41 while ((de = readdir(d)) != NULL) {
42 char *tmpname;
43
44 if (streq(de->d_name, ".")
45 || streq(de->d_name, ".."))
46 continue;
47
48 tmpname = join_path(dirname, de->d_name);
49
50 if (lstat(tmpname, &st) < 0)
51 die("stat(%s): %s\n", tmpname, strerror(errno));
52
53 if (S_ISREG(st.st_mode)) {
54 struct property *prop;
55 FILE *pfile;
56
57 pfile = fopen(tmpname, "rb");
58 if (! pfile) {
59 fprintf(stderr,
60 "WARNING: Cannot open %s: %s\n",
61 tmpname, strerror(errno));
62 } else {
63 prop = build_property(xstrdup(de->d_name),
64 data_copy_file(pfile,
65 st.st_size));
66 add_property(tree, prop);
67 fclose(pfile);
68 }
69 } else if (S_ISDIR(st.st_mode)) {
70 struct node *newchild;
71
72 newchild = read_fstree(tmpname);
73 newchild = name_node(newchild, xstrdup(de->d_name));
74 add_child(tree, newchild);
75 }
76
77 free(tmpname);
78 }
79
80 closedir(d);
81 return tree;
82}
83
84struct dt_info *dt_from_fs(const char *dirname)
85{
86 struct node *tree;
87
88 tree = read_fstree(dirname);
89 tree = name_node(tree, "");
90
91 return build_dt_info(DTSF_V1, NULL, tree, guess_boot_cpuid(tree));
92}
